text: Quinta Steenbergen (born April 2, 1985 in Schagen) is a Dutch volleyball player, who plays as a Center. She was a member of the Women's National Team. She plays for VK AGEL Prostějov. ==Personal== Steenbergen has one older brother and two older sisters. ==Clubs== * AMVJ Amstelveen (2001–2003) * VC Weert (2003–2004) * AMVJ Amstelveen (2004–2008) * Rocheville Le Cannet (2008–2009) * TVC Amstelveen (2010–2011) * VC Baku (2011–2012) * Schweriner SC (2012–2013) * VK AGEL Prostějov (2013–2014) * Lokomotiv Baku (2014–2015) * VK AGEL Prostějov (2015–2016) ==References== ==External links== * FIVB Profile Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch women's volleyball players Category:Dutch expatriates in Germany Category:People from Schagen Category:Expatriate volleyball players in France Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Germany Category:Lokomotiv Baku volleyball players Category:European Games competitors for the Netherlands Category:Volleyball players at the 2015 European Games Category:Volleyball players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Azerbaijan Category:Expatriate volleyball players in the Czech Republic Category:Dutch expatriates in France Category:Dutch expatriates in Azerbaijan Category:Dutch expatriates in the Czech Republic Category:Olympic volleyball players of the Netherlands
